.SH "NAME"
skb_copy \- create private copy of an sk_buff
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'struct\ sk_buff\ *\ skb_copy('u
.BI "struct sk_buff * skb_copy(const\ struct\ sk_buff\ *\ " "skb" ", gfp_t\ " "gfp_mask" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIskb\fR
.RS 4
buffer to copy
.RE
.PP
\fIgfp_mask\fR
.RS 4
allocation priority
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Make a copy of both an
sk_buff
and its data\&. This is used when the caller wishes to modify the data and needs a private copy of the data to alter\&. Returns
\fBNULL\fR
on failure or the pointer to the buffer on success\&. The returned buffer has a reference count of 1\&.
.PP
As by\-product this function converts non\-linear
sk_buff
to linear one, so that
sk_buff
becomes completely private and caller is allowed to modify all the data of returned buffer\&. This means that this function is not recommended for use in circumstances when only header is going to be modified\&. Use
\fBpskb_copy\fR
instead\&.
